Audio file analysis :
====================

Design Ideas  :
================

To achieve text-to-speech (TTS) playback for 80+ short phrases (e.g., "Color Red", "Pattern Stars", "Letter A"), you‚Äôll want a balance of:

‚úÖ Clear, recognizable speech

‚úÖ Efficient storage (minimize .wav file size)

‚úÖ Fast playback

‚úÖ Offline capability (no cloud needed)

üìÅ .WAV File Size Estimation
==============================
Assumptions:

16-bit mono audio

16 kHz sample rate (good quality for speech)

PCM encoded

Each phrase is ~1 second long (or less)

üíæ Size Per File:
16,000 samples/sec * 2 bytes/sample = ~32 KB/sec


So for a 1-second .wav file:
~32 KB per phrase

Total Estimation (Approx)
============================

| Type     | Count | Est. per file              | Total size |
| -------- | ----- | -------------------------- | ---------- |
| Letters  | 26    | 32 KB                      | \~832 KB   |
| Colors   | 80    | 32 KB                      | \~2.56 MB  |
| Patterns | 80    | 32 KB                      | \~2.56 MB  |
| Songs    | 80    | (longer, say 10s) \~320 KB | \~25 MB    |

üéµ Songs Are Bigger
===================

If each song is 10 seconds long (e.g., ‚ÄúPlay Twinkle Twinkle‚Äù), you get:

320 KB per song

******* ESP32 can handle SD cards easily for large file storage ******

80 songs ‚Üí ~25 MB total

Summary : 
========

| Task                   | Details                               |
| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| File type              | WAV (PCM) or MP3 (compressed)         |
| Size per speech phrase | \~32 KB (WAV), \~8 KB (MP3)           |
| Total phrases          | \~320 (80x4 types)                    |
| Storage needed         | \~10 MB (compressed) to \~30 MB       |
| Best playback method   | Use I2S DAC (e.g., MAX98357A)         |
| Storage medium         | Use **microSD*** |

